theorem Topology.closure_union_closure_right_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A ∪ closure B) = closure (A ∪ B) := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- `closure (A ∪ closure B) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`
    have h_subset : (A ∪ closure B : Set X) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
      intro x hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hxA =>
          -- `x ∈ A ⊆ A ∪ B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`
          have : (x : X) ∈ A ∪ B := Or.inl hxA
          exact subset_closure this
      | inr hxClB =>
          -- `closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)` by monotonicity of `closure`
          have h_closure_subset : closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
            apply closure_mono
            intro y hy
            exact Or.inr hy
          exact h_closure_subset hxClB
    exact closure_mono h_subset
  · -- `closure (A ∪ B) ⊆ closure (A ∪ closure B)`
    have h_subset : (A ∪ B : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ closure B := by
      intro x hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hxA =>
          exact Or.inl hxA
      | inr hxB =>
          exact Or.inr (subset_closure hxB)
    exact closure_mono h_subset
